---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Ana Rita Gomes" description="Ana Rita Gomes — Technical Writer, Knowledge Manager, former Software Engineer.">
  <div class="py-20 max-w-[70ch]">
    <header class="mb-14">
      <p class="font-mono text-[#7B35E4] text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-[#e8e8f0] mb-0">Ana Rita Gomes</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-[#6b6b80] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I'm a Technical Writer and Knowledge Manager based in Portugal.
      </p>
      <p>
        I came to this work from software engineering — almost a decade of it, across telecoms, insurance, and research. I have an MSc in AI from the University of Leeds. At some point I realised I cared less about building systems than about making sure people could actually understand and use them.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe documentation matters. Not as a formality, not as something you do after the real work is done — but as the thing that determines whether knowledge stays inside one person's head or becomes useful to everyone else. Most organisations treat it as an afterthought. I find that genuinely frustrating, which is probably why I ended up making it my job.
      </p>
      <p>
        I like explaining things. I like finding the right structure for complicated information. And I think knowledge sharing — done properly — is one of the most underrated things a team can invest in.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="mailto:anaritacruzgomes@gmail.com" class="text-[#7B35E4] hover:underline font-mono text-sm">
          anaritacruzgomes@gmail.com
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
